Hi, I'm trying to make a workflow action with my app. I have everything set up where it shows most of the configuration.
My backend of the app can also receive the post request using the actionUrl and I'm using NodeJS client library to handle everything. I'm able to see the callback data when I look at the events of the flow.

The issue im having is that my `outputFields` configuration is not showing and instead only shows `This action's final success or failure state`. The documentation explains how to configure this but the client library does not have this defined as a field. Is it not supported yet? Is there another way I can do this?
```{
  'outputFields': [
        {
            'typeDefinition': {
                'name': 'placeholder',
                'type': 'string',
                'fieldType': 'text'
            }
        }
    ],
    'labels': {
        'en': {
             ...
            'outputFieldLabels':{
                'placeholder': 'label'
            },
        }
    }
}```
Any advice or guidance is greatly appreciated, thanks!

This my actual request to the api, im updating since its already made.
```await hbClient.automation.actions.definitionsApi.update(workflowResponse.results[0].id,process.env.APP_ID, workflowExtensionConfigV3 );```
